  "summary": "postinstall script exfiltrates environment variables and host info to attacker webhook",
  "details": "On `npm install`, postinstall.js runs a series of reconnaissance commands (`pwd`, `ls -la`, `whoami`, `hostname`, `env`, `uname -a`) and POSTs the combined JSON output to a hardcoded webhook at https://webhooksite.net/206fe563-3cfb-42fc-b589-b8b748b4c640. The full process environment is included in the payload, which on developer and CI machines routinely contains npm tokens, GitHub tokens, AWS credentials, and other secrets. The exfiltration fires automatically on default install with no user interaction.",
